text: This area is more peaceful and less crowded than the park across the road. Many people go there with more sports activities going on so this place seems more relaxing. COVID Phase 2 currently so the water play for kids  is still not open, and playground is also not as crowded as across the road. Overall a nice walk in the park literally!

I came on a short visit to the Burp restaurant.

On the walk from the open air carpark to the restaurant, my kids spotted chickens, otters etc. The waterway passing through is nicely "decorated" by plants to merge the storm drain up to the walking tracks. Beautiful mature trees with ferns planted with them. They make a great pair.

My favourite place for exercise. Best to go after 10am as not so crowded. You can sure to see chicken, squirrel everywhere. Sometimes can see migrant birds, ducks, parrot, otters.  I once saw a chameleon.
Lovely bird watching walk along with birds sound and the river sound.. perfect place for nature lovers
